Japan 's seasonally adjusted unemployment rate rose record 3.0 pct January , worst since Government started compiling unemployment statistic current system 1953 , previous record 2.9 pct December , government 's Management Coordination Agency said .
Unemployment 2.8 pct year earlier .
Unadjusted January unemployment totalled 1.82 mln people , 1.61 mln December 1.65 mln year earlier .
Male unemployment January remained 2.9 pct , equal second-worst level set last December .
Record male unemployement 3.1 pct set July 1986 .
Female unemployment January remained 3.0 pct , equal record level marked April , August , September December last year .
January 's record 3.0 pct unemployment rate mainly stemmed loss job manufacturing industry , particularly export-related firm , due yen 's continuing appreciation dollar , official said .
Employment manufacturing industry fell 380,000 year earlier 14.30 mln including 1.83 mln employed textile industry , 190,000 year earlier , 1.06 mln transport industry carmaker shipbuilder , 170,000 .
